Ex. No:  — Compute Summary Statistics using Python
Aim

To compute mean, median, and standard deviation using Python.

Theory

Summary statistics help understand the distribution of data.

Mean → Average value
Median → Middle value
Standard Deviation → Spread of data

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
NumPy and Pandas Libraries



Program
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# Dataset
marks = [55, 65, 75, 85, 95]

# DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame({'Marks': marks})

# Statistics
mean_value = df['Marks'].mean()
median_value = df['Marks'].median()
std_value = df['Marks'].std()

print("Dataset:")
print(df)

print("\nMean:", mean_value)
print("Median:", median_value)
print("Standard Deviation:", std_value)



Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import NumPy and Pandas.
Create dataset of marks.
Convert data into DataFrame.
Use mean() function.
Use median() function.
Use std() function.
Store statistical values.
Display results.
Verify output.


